                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode3/custom-serialization-field.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <h2 id="the-serialization-visitor">The Serialization Visitor <a class="headerlink" href="custom-serialization-field#the-serialization-visitor" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>Back in the subscriber, create a new variable called <code>$visitor</code> and set it to
<code>$event-&gt;getVisitor()</code>. The visitor is kind of in charge of the serialization
process. And since we <em>know</em> we're serializing to JSON, this will be an instance
of <code>JsonSerializationVisitor</code>. Write an inline doc for that and add a use statement
up top. That will give us autocompletion:</p>
